SIMPLE: phlox
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: phlox
<hw>phlox</hw> <pr>(fl⟦ocr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a kind of
flower, fr. Gr. <grk>flo`x</grk> flame, fr. <grk>fle`gein</grk> to
burn.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of American herbs, having
showy red, white, or purple flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Phlox worm</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the larva of
an American moth (<spn>Heliothis phloxiphaga</spn>). It is destructive
to phloxes.</cd> -- <col><b>Phlox subulata</b></col>, <cd>the moss pink.
See under <er>Moss</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phlyctenular</ent>⟦br⟧
